+# False Positive Analysis: CVE-2026-31802 in tar v6.1.14
+
+## Summary
+
+**CVE-2026-31802 does not affect tar v6.1.14.**
+
+The vulnerable code path — drive-relative symlink resolution via
+`path.posix.join(entryDir, p)` in `src/unpack.ts` — was introduced in
+the v7.x TypeScript rewrite of node-tar and has never existed in the v6.x
+JavaScript codebase.
+
+---
+
+## CVE Overview
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| CVE ID | CVE-2026-31802 |
+| GHSA ID | GHSA-9ppj-qmqm-q256 |
+| CVSS Score | 8.2 (v4.0) |
+| Severity | HIGH |
+| CWE | CWE-22 (Path Traversal) |
+| Published | 2026-03-09 |
+| Fix Commit | f48b5fa3b7985ddab96dc0f2125a4ffc9911b6ad |
+| Fix Version | 7.5.11 |
+
+**Description**: node-tar versions prior to 7.5.11 can be tricked into creating
+a symlink that points outside the extraction directory by using a drive-relative
+symlink target (e.g., `C:../../../target.txt`), enabling file overwrite outside
+cwd during normal `tar.x()` extraction.
+
+---
+
+## Why v6.1.14 Is Not Affected
+
+### 1. Different source file — fix target does not exist in v6.x
+
+The upstream fix modifies `src/unpack.ts` (TypeScript), which **does not exist**
+in tar v6.1.14. The v6.x line uses `lib/unpack.js` (JavaScript) with a
+completely different CHECKPATH implementation.
+
+### 2. Different language and architecture
+
+tar v7.x is a TypeScript rewrite of the library. The drive-relative symlink
+resolution logic (`path.posix.join(entryDir, p)` for symlink linkpath resolution
+relative to the entry directory) was **introduced** in the v7.x rewrite and never
+backported to v6.x.
+
+### 3. v6.1.14's CHECKPATH rejects the attack vector by design
+
+In `lib/unpack.js` (v6.1.14), the `CHECKPATH` function uses a simpler approach:
+- `parts.includes('..')` rejects any path containing `..` segments.
+- `/^[a-z]:\.\.$/i.test(parts[0])` specifically rejects Windows drive-relative
+  patterns such as `C:..`.
+
+This means the class of inputs that CVE-2026-31802 exploits in v7.x are already
+blocked at path validation time in v6.1.14. The sophisticated symlink linkpath
+resolution relative to the entry directory (`path.posix.join(entryDir, p)`) that
+introduces the vulnerability in v7.x **does not exist** in v6.1.14.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendation
+
+No patch is required. Dismiss scanner findings for CVE-2026-31802 against
+tar v6.1.14 with:
+
+> The vulnerable drive-relative symlink path resolution code (`path.posix.join`
+> in `src/unpack.ts`) was introduced in the tar v7.x TypeScript rewrite.
+> tar v6.1.14 uses `lib/unpack.js` with a different architecture that does not
+> contain the vulnerable code path.

